        	<div class="site-content"><div class="wp-block-kadence-rowlayout alignfull"><div id="kt-layout-id_61ee3c-fa" class="kt-row-layout-inner kt-row-has-bg kt-layout-id_61ee3c-fa"><div class="kt-row-layout-overlay kt-row-overlay-gradient"></div><div class="kt-row-column-wrap kt-has-2-columns kt-gutter-default kt-v-gutter-default kt-row-valign-middle kt-row-layout-equal kt-tab-layout-equal kt-m-colapse-right-to-left kt-mobile-layout-row  kt-custom-first-width-60  kt-custom-second-width-40"><div class="wp-block-kadence-column inner-column-1 kadence-column_84ec52-24"><div class="kt-inside-inner-col"><h2 class="kt-adv-heading_8f91f6-7e wp-block-kadence-advancedheading" data-kb-block="kb-adv-heading_8f91f6-7e"><span style="color: #ffffff;" class="stk-highlight">Sensory Trail Consultation</span></h2>

<p>A sensory trail is appropriate for everyone to enjoy and is designed to stimulate our senses through touch, scent, sight, taste and hearing. This will be done mainly through various planting schemes but will include some construction work if approved.</p></div></div>

<div class="wp-block-kadence-column inner-column-2 kadence-column_5ee31e-b7 kvs-sm-false"><div class="kt-inside-inner-col"><figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" width="321" height="321" src="https://bhhub.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/Hike-routes_320px.png" alt="" class="wp-image-4430" srcset="https://bhhub.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/Hike-routes_320px.png 321w, https://bhhub.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/Hike-routes_320px-300x300.png 300w, https://bhhub.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/Hike-routes_320px-150x150.png 150w, https://bhhub.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/Hike-routes_320px-100x100.png 100w, https://bhhub.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/Hike-routes_320px-50x50.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 321px) 100vw, 321px" /></figure></div></div></div></div></div><div class="wp-block-kadence-column inner-column-1 kadence-column_1b0202-b7"><div class="kt-inside-inner-col"><p>The public consultation on the possible development of a sensory trail around the perimeter<br>of the Bishops Hull Playing Field commences on Saturday 12th November. The plans will also be available here and on notice boards around the village for the month of November. We are looking for feedback as soon as possible, but no later than Wednesday 30th November, to gauge the level of interest in the project from the community.</p>

